en. Along the way, Zanini De Vita debunks such culinary myths as Marco Polo's supposed role in pasta's story even as she serves up a feast of new information. Encyclopedia of Pasta, illustrated throughout with original drawings by Luciana Marini, will be the standard reference on one of the world's favorite foods for many years to come, engaging and delighting both general readers and food professionals.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCooking (Pasta). 0aPasta productszItalyvEncyclopedias. 0aPasta productszItalyxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh  acookbook.  acookbooks italian.  acooking.  afamily recipes.  afood and culture.  afood and diet.  afood lovers.  afood prep.  afood reference.  afood scholars.  afood.  ageographical.  agnocchi.  ahistorical.  ahistory of food.  ahistory of pasta.  ahome cooks.  aillustrated.  aitalian pasta.  aitaly.  akitchen setting.  amediterranean foods.  anonfiction.  aoral histories.  apasta lovers.  apasta recipes.  apasta.  apreparation techniques.  aravioli.  aregional cuisine.  aspaghetti.  astaple food.  astrascinati.  atagliatelle.  avincisgrassi.1 aBarberis, Corrado, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFant, Maureen B, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aField, Carol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZanini De Vita, Oretta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025522740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094471840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9